radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal bibasilar atelectasis; small pericardial effusion; unremarkable liver, spleen, right kidney, and pancreas; small amount of intermediate attenuation density in both post-surgical beds; gallbladder wall edema; unremarkable small and large bowel; shotty retroperitoneal adenopathy; small amount of fluid with focus of air and stranding in anterior abdominal wall subcutaneous tissues; unremarkable rectum, sigmoid colon, and bladder; multiple calcified fibroids; mild lower lumbar degenerative joint disease.
